<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>Ahara Support</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <style>
    :root {
      --primary: #4b2e83;
      --primary-light: #f3ecff;
      --accent: #ff9f1c;
      --text: #222222;
      --muted: #666666;
      --bg: #f7f7fb;
      --card-bg: #ffffff;
      --radius-lg: 18px;
    }

    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI",
        sans-serif;
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--text);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    header {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ffb347, #ffcc33);
      padding: 32px 16px 40px;
      text-align: center;
      color: #fff;
    }

    .logo-circle {
      width: 78px;
      height: 78px;
      border-radius: 24px;
      margin: 0 auto 12px;
      background: #ffffff22;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      font-size: 28px;
      font-weight: 800;
      text-shadow: 0 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25);
    }

    header h1 {
      margin: 0 0 6px;
      font-size: 28px;
      letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    }

    header p {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 15px;
      opacity: 0.95;
    }

    main {
      max-width: 920px;
      margin: -28px auto 40px;
      padding: 0 16px;
    }

    .card {
      background: var(--card-bg);
      border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
      padding: 20px 18px;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
      box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.08);
    }

    .card h2 {
      margin-top: 0;
      font-size: 20px;
    }

    .pill {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 2px 10px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      font-size: 11px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      background: var(--primary-light);
      color: var(--primary);
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 6px;
    }

    .section-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1.25fr 1fr;
      gap: 16px;
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .section-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }

    ul {
      padding-left: 20px;
      margin-top: 6px;
    }

    li + li {
      margin-top: 4px;
    }

    .highlight {
      background: #fff8e6;
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 12px 12px;
      font-size: 14px;
    }

    a {
      color: var(--primary);
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-decoration-thickness: 1.5px;
      text-underline-offset: 2px;
    }

    .faq-item + .faq-item {
      margin-top: 10px;
      padding-top: 10px;
      border-top: 1px solid #eee;
    }

    .faq-question {
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 2px;
    }

    .muted {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 13px;
    }

    footer {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 24px 16px 32px;
      font-size: 12px;
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    code {
      font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Liberation Mono",
        "Courier New", monospace;
      font-size: 12px;
      background: #f3f3f8;
      padding: 2px 4px;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <div class="logo-circle">a</div>
    <h1>Ahara Support</h1>
    <p>Help, feedback, and account management for the Ahara app.</p>
  </header>

  <main>
    <!-- About Ahara -->
    <section class="card">
      <span class="pill">About</span>
      <h2>What is Ahara?</h2>
      <p>
        Ahara helps groups coordinate food orders and catering more easily. You
        can create a group, invite members, collect orders, and track
        everything in one place.
      </p>
      <p class="muted">
        Platform availability: iOS and Android (including closed testing on
        Google Play while we finish development).
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact & Support -->
    <section class="card section-grid">
      <div>
        <span class="pill">Support</span>
        <h2>Contact & Help</h2>
        <p>
          If you need help with Ahara, have a question, or want to report a
          problem, you can reach us here:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Email:</strong>
            <a href="mailto:support@ahara-hub.com">support@ahara-hub.com</a>
          </li>
          <!-- You can change this to your real website when ready -->
          <li>
            <strong>Website:</strong>
            <a href="https://ahara-hub.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              https://ahara-hub.com
            </a>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="muted">
          When contacting support, please include the email address you use in
          Ahara and (if applicable) your device type (iPhone / Android).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <span class="pill">Quick links</span>
        <div class="highlight">
          <strong>Common topics</strong>
          <ul style="margin-top:6px;">
            <li>Inviting people to your group</li>
            <li>Trouble signing in</li>
            <li>Deleting a group you own</li>
            <li>Deleting your Ahara account</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Account Deletion -->
    <section id="account-deletion" class="card">
      <span class="pill">Account</span>
      <h2>How to delete your Ahara account</h2>
      <p>
        You can permanently delete your Ahara account directly from within the
        app. Deleting your account removes your profile and signs you out. You
        may lose access to your groups and related data.
      </p>

      <h3>Delete your account in the app</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Open the <strong>Ahara</strong> app on your device.</li>
        <li>Sign in with the account you wish to delete.</li>
        <li>
          Go to any group’s main screen (where you see the
          <strong>Members</strong> and <strong>Orders</strong> tabs).
        </li>
        <li>
          In the top-right corner, tap the
          <strong>⋯ (three-dot)</strong> menu.
        </li>
        <li>Select <strong>Delete Account</strong>.</li>
        <li>
          Read the confirmation message carefully, then tap
          <strong>Delete</strong> to confirm.
        </li>
      </ol>

      <p class="muted">
        Note: In some cases, for security reasons, you may be asked to sign in
        again before your account can be deleted. This is required by our
        authentication provider to verify that you are the account owner.
      </p>

      <h3>If you can’t access the app</h3>
      <p>
        If you no longer have access to the app or the email address you used
        to sign up, you can request account deletion by contacting support:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Email us at
          <a href="mailto:support@ahara-hub.com">support@ahara-hub.com</a>
        </li>
        <li>Use the subject line: <code>Account Deletion Request</code></li>
        <li>
          Include the email address and phone number you used in Ahara, and any
          group names you remember.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="muted">
        We may ask for additional information to confirm ownership before
        processing the deletion request.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Deleting a group -->
    <section class="card">
      <span class="pill">Groups</span>
      <h2>Deleting a group you own</h2>
      <p>
        Only the group owner can delete a group. Deleting a group removes it
        for all members.
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>Open the <strong>Ahara</strong> app and sign in.</li>
        <li>Go to the group you own.</li>
        <li>
          On the group main screen, tap the <strong>⋯ (three-dot)</strong> menu
          in the top-right.
        </li>
        <li>Select <strong>Delete Group</strong>.</li>
        <li>Confirm when prompted.</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="muted">
        This action cannot be undone. Existing messages and orders may be
        permanently removed or become inaccessible.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="card">
      <span class="pill">FAQ</span>
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
          I didn’t receive the invite link. What should I do?
        </div>
        <div>
          Ask the group owner to resend the invite via SMS or WhatsApp, and
          make sure your device can open links. If you’re on Android closed
          testing, confirm that you’ve accepted the testing program in Google
          Play.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
          The invite link opens but I don’t see the app in the store.
        </div>
        <div>
          On Android, ensure you are signed in to the same Google account that
          was added as a tester. On iOS, check that you are using the correct
          App Store region if Ahara is only available in selected countries.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
          Can I recover my account after it has been deleted?
        </div>
        <div>
          No. Account deletion is permanent. Once your Ahara account has been
          deleted, we are generally unable to restore it.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
          How can I report a bug or request a feature?
        </div>
        <div>
          Email us at
          <a href="mailto:support@ahara-hub.com">support@ahara-hub.com</a> with
          as much detail as possible (screenshots, steps to reproduce, device
          model). We appreciate your feedback and use it to improve Ahara.
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Privacy / Data -->
    <section class="card">
      <span class="pill">Privacy</span>
      <h2>Data & Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Ahara uses Firebase services (Authentication, Firestore, and
        Messaging) to provide secure sign-in, store group and order information,
        and deliver notifications.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          We collect basic account information you provide (such as name, email,
          and phone number).
        </li>
        <li>
          We use this information only to operate the app and communicate with
          you about your account.
        </li>
        <li>
          You can request deletion of your account and associated personal data
          at any time using the steps above.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="muted">
        For more details or specific privacy questions, please contact us at
        <a href="mailto:support@ahara-hub.com">support@ahara-hub.com</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer>
    © <span id="year"></span> Ahara. All rights reserved.
  </footer>

  <script>
    document.getElementById("year").textContent = new Date().getFullYear();
  </script>
</body>
</html>
